CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper November 1, 1952, pg. 21, reads: "Father-Son Jamboree - Everyone was an Indian when the Centre Avenue YMCA held its annual Father and Son Jamboree in the gymnasium last week. The youngsters and their fathers heard a talk by a real Indian Chief and saw him give an exhibition of much of the Indian lore he had been taught. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Crowd, including boys wearing paper feather headbands, gathered around man in Native American dress, for father - son jamboree in Centre Avenue YMCA
